description: This tutorial is on how to filter rows of a dataframe based on conditions on columns in dataframe in Python.
Keywords: date, datetime, python, tutorial, manish barnwal


df.loc[:, ['col1', 'col2']]

df.loc[df.browser == 'Chrome', :]
df.browser.sample(10)

df.loc[df.browser.isin(['Chrome', 'IE']), :]


Dropping columns

df.drop(labels=['col1', 'col2'], axis=1, inplace=True)
